pistomp-recovery (0.1.0-25) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Fix nav-encoder click not registering on pi-Stomp Core (v2): the button
    is wired to a plain GPIO pin there (matching pi-stomp's
    pistompcore.py sw_pin=1), not the MCP3008 ADC channel 4 used on Tre (v3).
    GpioInputBackend now picks GpioSwitch on v2 and AdcSwitch on v3 via the
    shared hardware/version.py::is_v2() detector.
  * Support the Tweak knob on pi-Stomp Core, where it's a fixed-sweep
    potentiometer on a builder-configured ADC channel rather than a rotary
    encoder like Tre's fixed-pin tweak1. hardware/version.py::
    tweak_adc_channels() reads the live default_config.yml's
    hardware.analog_controllers so recovery works whether the box has Tweak 1,
    Tweak 2, or both populated. The new TweakPot (hardware/tweak_pot.py) maps
    the pot's absolute position directly to a step index (leftmost = step 0,
    rightmost = step 39) and emits LEFT/RIGHT events to walk the current step
    to match — since a bare pot doesn't spring back to center like a
    joystick, this avoids a rate-based scheme getting stuck scrolling until
    manually returned to an unmarked middle position. InputManager now polls
    a list of tweak inputs instead of a single fixed one.

 -- Cam Gorrie <sastraxi@gmail.com>  Thu, 09 Jul 2026 23:06:57 +0000

