pistomp-recovery (0.1.0-18) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Fix crash recovery going unnoticed: _service_crashed only checked systemd's
    Result property when ActiveState was "inactive", but OnFailure fires
    immediately on a crash and Restart=always has usually moved the unit back to
    "activating" or "active" by the time recovery's Python runs. Result persists
    across all ActiveState transitions (reset only on a successful start), so
    it is now checked regardless of state. Verified against exit-code, signal
    (SIGKILL/SEGV), ImportError, and SyntaxError crashes — all now correctly
    show the CrashScreen with the traceback instead of the main menu.

 -- Cam Gorrie <sastraxi@gmail.com>  Wed, 01 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000

pistomp-recovery (0.1.0-17) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Skip package-delivered LV2 bundles when performing a factory plugin reset
    so the apt/OTA-maintained copy in /usr/lib/lv2 is never shadowed by the
    older factory tarball. The image builder records the affected bundle names
    to /etc/pistomp/factory-lv2-system-bundles.list at build time; recovery
    reads that list at runtime and skips matching members during streaming
    tar extraction. Older images without the list fall back to plain additive
    extraction with no bundles excluded.

