pistomp-recovery (0.1.0-13) trixie; urgency=medium

  * PluginFacet now supports stamp and checkpoint in addition to factory
    reset. A stamp file (PLUGINS_STAMP_FILE) records the known-good bundle
    set; pistomp-stamp adds bundles on successful install. Checkpoint shows
    bundles installed since the last stamp with a "Rollback to stamp" action
    that deletes them; stamped-but-missing bundles appear as informational
    rows. A factory allowlist (FACTORY_LV2_BUNDLES_FILE, one bundle dir per
    line) prevents factory-shipped bundles from being deleted even if they
    carry the PatchStorage marker.
  * Updates picker shows only the System domain. domains(mode) now accepts a
    mode parameter; for "updates" mode all backends return only System, since
    pedalboards and plugins have no installable updates via recovery.
  * Checkpoint mode preserves clean items with no rollback action as
    informational rows, so the user can see their full stamped state even for
    items that are already at checkpoint.
  * pistomp-stamp refactored to use subcommands (stamp/status) with --pedalboard
    and --plugin flags. Stamps plugins facet globally; --plugin <name> appends
    a single bundle to the stamp set. Backward-compatible: the old positional
    form (pistomp-stamp stamp <bundle-path>) still works.

 -- pistomp <pistomp@example.com>  Thu, 25 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

pistomp-recovery (0.1.0-12) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Fix the landscape-native port rendering the LCD upside-down on the Tre.
    The port had copied pi-stomp's LcdIli9341.flip convention (flip=True ->
    MADCTL 0x28, no mirror), but recovery's flip parameter has the opposite
    historical meaning (flip=True -> 180-degree rotation -> mirror both axes
    -> MADCTL 0xE8). Swap the mapping so the default LcdSpi() call site
    keeps the panel upright.

 -- pistomp <pistomp@example.com>  Thu, 25 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

pistomp-recovery (0.1.0-11) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Fix dirty-rect partial updates rendering vertically flipped on the LCD
    (title bar appeared at the bottom, content reversed, top of the panel
    never repainted). Port pi-stomp's landscape-native ILI9341 driver:
    init() rewrites MADCTL to 0xE8/0x28 so 320x240 surface coords map
    straight to the panel address window, and both full and partial pushes
    share one _block_fast path (numpy RGB565 pack, single SPI lock/CS, os.write
    chunked by SPIDEV_BUFSIZ) with no per-push rotation or coordinate swap.
  * Drop the adafruit_rgb_display image_to_data monkeypatch (driver_patch):
    the hot update() path now bypasses image_to_data entirely, so the patch
    is dead weight.

 -- pistomp <pistomp@example.com>  Thu, 25 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000

pistomp-recovery (0.1.0-10) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Re-issue.
  * After a successful package install, restart any affected services that are
    currently active (e.g. browsepy, mod-touchosc2midi) rather than asking the
    user to exit recovery; pistomp-recovery restarts itself via systemd when it
    is among the installed packages.
  * Do not stamp packages after an install — the stamp should only be written
    by pistomp-stamp when pi-Stomp successfully loads, so rollback-to-stamp
    remains a meaningful revert target.
  * Fix services_for_packages() dropping services not in PISTOMP_SERVICES
    (e.g. mod-touchosc2midi was silently omitted); add mod-touchosc2midi to
    the ordering chain.
  * Partial-redraw (dirty-rect) support: MenuScreen tracks which rows changed
    and flushes only those rectangles over SPI, reducing typical frame transfer
    time from a full-screen blit to a small clip.

